		<td width="550" align="left" valign="top" style="font-family:'Century Gothic',Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:18px;line-height:22px;color:#010101"><strong>SUPPORT WORKER ROLES</strong></td>
		
		<td width="25" align="left" valign="top"></td>
		
		</tr>
		
		<tr>
		
		<td width="25" align="left" valign="top"></td>
		
		<td width="550" align="center" valign="top"><img src="http://www.ncsthechallenge.org/images/staffing/Images/ncstc_hr_290914.jpg" width="550" height="22" border="0" style="display:block"></td>
		
		<td width="25" align="left" valign="top"></td>
		
		</tr>
		
		<tr>
		
		<td width="25" align="left" valign="top"></td>
		
		<td width="550" align="left" valign="top" style="font-family:'Century Gothic',Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:15px;line-height:20px;color:#222222"><p>The<strong>Support Worker Role</strong> focuses on the one-to-one support of a young person with additional requirements as they take part in our seasonal programme.</p>
		
		<p>The role requires a patient, enthusiastic and experienced individual to ensure that their young person participates to their full potential, achieves their own personal goals and integrates fully with their team.</p>
		
		<p>Experience of working with young people with challenging behaviour and/or additional requirements is ideal for this intense and rewarding role.</p></td>
		
		<td width="25" align="left" valign="top"></td>
		
		</tr>
		
		<tr>
		
		<td width="600" height="50" colspan="3" align="center" valign="top"></td>
		
		</tr>
		
		<tr>
		
		<td width="25" align="left" valign="top"></td>
		
		<td width="550" align="left" valign="top" style="font-family:'Century Gothic',Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:18px;line-height:22px;color:#010101"><strong>OTHER PAID OPPORTUNITIES</strong></td>
		
		<td width="25" align="left" valign="top"></td>
		
		</tr>
		
		<tr>
		
		<td width="25" align="left" valign="top"></td>
		
		<td width="550" align="center" valign="top"><img src="http://www.ncsthechallenge.org/images/staffing/Images/ncstc_hr_290914.jpg" width="550" height="22" border="0" style="display:block"></td>
		
		<td width="25" align="left" valign="top"></td>
		
		</tr>
		
		<tr>
		
		<td width="25" align="left" valign="top"></td>
		
		<td width="550" align="left" valign="top" style="font-family:'Century Gothic',Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:15px;line-height:20px;color:#222222"><p><strong>Leader Roles</strong> Lead between 60 and 84 young people and up to 15 staff members through a complex and demanding programme. You will also be responsible for challenging behaviour during residential stays.</p>
		
		<p><strong>Mentor Roles</strong> Facilitate, lead and pastorally care for your team, ensuring the personal development of each young person while undertaking various exciting activities.</p>
		
		<p><strong>Logistical Roles</strong> Assist with the logistical management of different weeks of the programme, managing relationships with key partners and young people.</p>

<p><strong>Practitioner Roles</strong> Deliver skill-building activities using sport, media, drama, photography, enterprise or music, and show your teams how your skill can make a difference in the community.
		
		<p><strong>Many of our roles have a residential element to them. Please check individual role descriptions on <a href="http://www.ncsthechallenge.org/seasonal-roles" target="_blank">www.ncsthechallenge.org/seasonal-roles</a> for more details.</strong></p>
		
		<p><a href="http://ncsthechallenge.org/summer-staff-testimonials" target="_blank"><img src="https://staffing.the-challenge.org/assets/staffing_testimonials_screenshot.JPG" alt="Click to watch full clip" width="550" height="450" border="0" style="display:block"></a></p></td>
		
		<td width="25" align="left" valign="top"></td>
		
		</tr>
		
		<tr>
		
		<td width="600" height="50" colspan="3" align="center" valign="top"></td>
		
		</tr>
		
		<tr>
		
		<td width="25" align="left" valign="top"></td>
		
		<td width="550" align="left" valign="top" style="font-family:'Century Gothic',Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:18px;line-height:22px;color:#010101"><strong>OUR SEASONAL PROGRAMMES</strong></td>
		
		<td width="25" align="left" valign="top"></td>
		
		</tr>
		
		<tr>
		
		<td width="25" align="left" valign="top"></td>
		
		<td width="550" align="center" valign="top"><img src="http://www.ncsthechallenge.org/images/staffing/Images/ncstc_hr_290914.jpg" width="550" height="22" border="0" style="display:block"></td>
		
		<td width="25" align="left" valign="top"></td>
		
		</tr>
		
		<tr>
		
		<td width="25" align="left" valign="top"></td>
		
		<td width="550" align="left" valign="top" style="font-family:'Century Gothic',Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:15px;line-height:20px;color:#222222">
		
			<table width="550" align="center" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tbody><tr>
			
			<td align="left" valign="top"><p><strong>When can you work on NCS with The Challenge?</strong></p>
			
			<p>We run our seasonal youth programmes throughout the year.</p>
<p>Find out more about our seasonal roles at <strong><a href="http://www.ncsthechallenge.org/" target="_blank">www.ncsthechallenge.org/</a></strong></p>
			
			<p><strong>Spring Programme:</strong></p>
<p>February half-term with some weekends in March</p>
			
			<p><strong>Summer Programme:</strong></p>
<p>Late June to Early October</p>
			
			<p><strong>Autumn Programme:</strong></p>
<p>October half-term with some weekends in November</p></td>
			
			<td align="right" valign="top"><a href="http://www.ncsthechallenge.org/images/photos/ncstc_staff-sideimg-comm1_211014.jpg" target="_blank"><img src="https://staffing.the-challenge.org/assets/Community_volunteering.jpg" alt="" width="250" height="300" border="0"></a></td>
			
